items.title: Awesome Meteor
items.content_text:
### Collections

*   [quave:collections (‚≠ê23)](https://github.com/quavedev/collections) - Create collections in a standard way.

### REST

*   [maka:rest](https://atmospherejs.com/maka/rest) - automatically make your Meteor app accessible over HTTP and DDP alike.
*   [vatfree:restivus (‚≠ê1)](https://github.com/vatfree/meteor-restivus) - Make REST endpoints for your Meteor app with incredible ease.

### Administration

*   [zodern:pure-admin (‚≠ê20)](https://github.com/zodern/meteor-pure-admin) - An isolated, customizable admin panel for Meteor.

### Routers

*   [iron:router (‚≠ê2k)](https://github.com/iron-meteor/iron-router) - A router that works on the server and the browser, designed specifically for Meteor.

### Offline

*   [quave:pwa (‚≠ê5)](https://github.com/quavedev/pwa) - A Meteor package that allows you to configure your PWA.

### Mobile

*   [meteor-push (‚≠ê29)](https://github.com/activitree/meteor-push) - Push notifications for cordova (ios, android) browser (Chrome, Safari, Firefox).
*   [quave:universal-links (‚≠ê0)](https://github.com/quavedev/universal-links) - A Meteor package that allows you to expose your native iOS settings to enable Universal Links.

### Analytics

*   [quave:analytics (‚≠ê4)](https://github.com/quavedev/analytics) - A Meteor package that allows you to send your page views and more to Google Analytics.

### Scaffolding

*   [maka-cli (‚≠ê0)](https://github.com/maka-io/maka-cli) - Maka-CLI is a command line tool, which organizes a web application's file structure and automates everyday package installation tasks for various application frameworks.
